Adopted versioning schema: vMAJOR.MINOR.PATCH:
*MAJOR version is incremented when incompatible API changes are commited.
*MINOR version is incremented when new functionalities are commited, however the new implementation is still backward-compatible.
*PATCH version is incremented when backward-compatible bug fixes are commited.

The keys used are:
  !: fixed/modified feature, -: deleted feature, +: new feature


current (main branch) -- 26-04-2026
  ! Bumping every third-party GitHub Action to its first Node.js 24 major across all workflows: actions/checkout v3/v4 → v5, actions/upload-artifact v4 → v6, actions/download-artifact v4 → v7, codecov/codecov-action v4 → v5, softprops/action-gh-release v2 → v3. All five were running on Node.js 20, which GitHub is forcing to Node.js 24 from 2026-06-02 and removing entirely on 2026-09-16. Pinned at the smallest major that switched to Node.js 24 to minimize behavior drift.
  ! Fixing release.yml validate job: actions/download-artifact `name:` no longer accepts wildcards in v5+ — the trailing `*` in `packages-${{ matrix.distro.tag }}*` was always a bug, ignored by v4. Each per-distro upload uses a literal artifact name, so the download now matches exactly (and merge-multiple is dropped — only needed when downloading several artifacts at once).
  ! Fixing release.yml packages job: the `install nfpm` step uses curl, but the minimal debian:12/13, ubuntu:24.04, rocky:9 and fedora base images don't ship curl. Added curl (and tar on the deb side) to the bootstrap step so nfpm download succeeds across the whole matrix. Pass --allowerasing to the rpm bootstrap so dnf can swap rocky:9's curl-minimal for the regular curl package without conflict.
  ! Fixing CMakeLists.txt protobuf discovery on system-package distros: `find_package(Protobuf CONFIG REQUIRED)` failed on Debian 12/13, Ubuntu 24.04 and Fedora because the system protobuf packages ship FindProtobuf.cmake (MODULE) only, not protobuf-config.cmake (CONFIG). Now tries CONFIG first (so an upstream-installed protobuf still wins) then falls back to the MODULE path. Imported target name `protobuf::protoc` is identical in both modes (CMake ≥ 3.10), so the rest of the file is unchanged.
  ! Fixing autotools build on system-package distros (Debian 12/13, Ubuntu 24.04, Fedora): proto/Makefile.am hard-coded `--plugin=protoc-gen-grpc=/usr/local/bin/grpc_cpp_plugin` (the legacy install.sh-installed location); system gRPC packages put the plugin under /usr/bin. configure.ac now discovers it via `AC_PATH_PROG([GRPC_CPP_PLUGIN], [grpc_cpp_plugin], [/usr/local/bin/grpc_cpp_plugin])` and substitutes `@GRPC_CPP_PLUGIN@` into all 13 protoc invocations.
  ! Fixing autotools per-module Makefile.am files to plumb the pkg-config CFLAGS through. Debian/Ubuntu put jsoncpp headers under `/usr/include/jsoncpp/`, not directly on the default search path, so #include <json/json.h> failed with "No such file or directory". configure.ac now aggregates `JSONCPP/KAFKA/KAFKACPP/SPDLOG/PROTOBUF/GRPC/GRPCCPP_CFLAGS` into a `COLLECTOR_PKG_CFLAGS` substitution, and every src/*/Makefile.am (bridge, core, dataDelivery, dataManipulation, dataWrapper, proto, utils) appends it to its per-target `_CPPFLAGS`. Harmless extra `-I` flags on modules that don't use a particular dep; required for system-pkg distros.
  ! Fixing pkg/build/install_deps.sh on Rocky/RHEL/CentOS/AlmaLinux: protobuf-devel, libconfig-devel and librdkafka-devel live in the CRB (CodeReady Builder) repo on EL9, which is disabled by default. Script now installs dnf-plugins-core and runs `dnf config-manager --set-enabled crb` (with a powertools fallback for EL8) before installing build deps. epel-release install order swapped to come after CRB enablement.
  ! Adding `autoconf automake libtool` to install_deps.sh for every distro family (deb, fedora, rocky/rhel/centos/alma). build_collector.sh runs `./autogen.sh` (which calls autoreconf) for the autotools half of the build that produces libgrpc_collector.so; minimal CI base images don't ship these by default and the script was failing with `autoreconf: not found` before the autotools build could even start.
  ! Fixing CMakeLists.txt spdlog flag propagation on Fedora/EL: spdlog-devel on Fedora/EL is built with `-DSPDLOG_FMT_EXTERNAL=ON`, so `spdlog/fmt/fmt.h` `#include`s `spdlog/fmt/bundled/core.h` only when the SPDLOG_FMT_EXTERNAL macro is NOT defined. The macro travels via `pkg-config --cflags spdlog` (in `SPDLOG_CFLAGS_OTHER`); CMakeLists was using only `${SPDLOG_LIBRARIES}` and a hardcoded include dir, dropping the `-D` on the floor. Now uses `${SPDLOG_INCLUDE_DIRS}` from pkg-config + `add_compile_options(${SPDLOG_CFLAGS_OTHER})`.
  - Removing rocky-9 from the release.yml build matrix for v1.2.0 (still installable via doc/INSTALL-FROM-SOURCE.md). Reason: EL9's stock protobuf is 3.14, which predates the `has_*()` accessors for `oneof` members (added in protobuf 3.15). data_manipulation.cc uses `has_node_id_str() / has_subscription_id_str() / has_<type>_value()` on Cisco oneof fields — refactoring to the older `*_case() == kXValue` API is well-defined work but out of scope for this release. Tracked for v1.3.
  ! Fixing nfpm deb dependency SOVER drift across the deb matrix: bookworm/noble/trixie ship different SOVER for libconfig++ (9v5 vs 11), libjsoncpp (25 vs 26), libfmt (9 vs 10) and libspdlog (1.10/1.12/1.15). Smoke-test on debian:13 was failing because `libconfig++9v5/libjsoncpp25/libspdlog1.10` aren't on trixie. Switched to `|` alternation so a single .deb resolves on all three deb distros. Also dropped the bogus `libfmt-dev/libspdlog-dev` runtime deps (those are -dev pkgs, not runtime SONAME providers); added the missing `librdkafka++1` runtime dep that the C++ kafka wrapper needs.
  ! Fixing install_deps.sh GRPC_RUNTIME for trixie: I had assumed Debian 13 ships gRPC 1.66 (would have been a major bump from bookworm's 1.51), but it actually ships libgrpc++1.51t64 — same major SOVER as bookworm with the t64 ABI rename. The `libgrpc++1.66t64 | libgrpc++1.66` alternation neither matched any package on trixie, so apt failed at smoke-test install. Collapsed trixie/noble/jammy/oracular/plucky into a single t64 case using `libgrpc++1.51t64 | libgrpc++1.66t64` (1.66t64 left as forward-looking alternation in case of a future bump).


v1.2.0 -- 26-04-2026
  + Adding .github/workflows/coverage.yml — builds the unit tests with --coverage, runs ctest, runs gcovr filtered to src/utils/, uploads the report to Codecov on every push to main and every PR. Dynamic Codecov badge in README.md alongside the existing CI status badge and a new Release badge (all three on a single row). Local dry-run reports 80.8% line coverage / 100% function coverage on src/utils/{cfg_handler.cc,logs_handler.cc,peer_parser.cc}. .gitignore extended to swallow *.gcno/*.gcda/coverage.xml/build-cov/ artifacts.
  + Adding a `validate-package` CI job downstream of the package build. Fires per-distro in a CLEAN target-distro container (no build deps), apt/dnf-installs the freshly-built .deb/.rpm — catching missing or wrong runtime depends, which the build-container smoke step is blind to because all -dev/-devel pkgs are already present there. Standalone validation: assert the man page lands gzipped, /usr/bin symlink in place, systemd unit + example config installed; launch the daemon in foreground with a minimal zmq-delivery config; assert all four vendor sockets bind on 127.0.0.1:2000{7..10}; SIGTERM and assert clean exit. Library validation: assert the .so + header + .pc file are present; compile a tiny C dlopen probe that resolves every public bridge symbol (catches transitive runtime dep breakage on system gRPC). The release job (GitHub Release creation) now needs both `packages` and `validate` — broken packages cannot ship.
  + Adding native distro packaging via nfpm: `.deb` for Debian 12/13 + Ubuntu 24.04, `.rpm` for Fedora + Rocky/RHEL 9. Two flavors per distro — `mdt-dialout-collector` (standalone daemon: binary, systemd unit, example config, man page) and `mdt-dialout-collector-lib` (library variant for pmacct/pmtelemetryd: libgrpc_collector.so + C bridge header + pkg-config file). Both link against the distro's own gRPC; apt/dnf resolves the rest of the runtime deps automatically. 5 distros × 2 variants = 10 packages per release.
  + Adding .github/workflows/release.yml CI pipeline. Triggered on tag push (v*) and via manual dispatch. Matrix runs in parallel inside debian:12 / debian:13 / ubuntu:24.04 / rockylinux:9 / fedora:latest containers; each cell installs build deps, builds the standalone binary + library, runs nfpm twice (once per variant), smoke-tests the resulting package by installing it back into the same container, uploads artifacts. On tag push the pipeline additionally creates a GitHub Release with auto-generated notes and attaches every package.
  + Adding pkg/ directory: nfpm.standalone.yaml + nfpm.library.yaml (with deb/rpm overrides for the per-ecosystem dep names), systemd unit (mdt-dialout-collector.service with hardening: NoNewPrivileges, ProtectSystem=strict, ProtectHome, PrivateTmp), maintainer scripts (postinstall creates the mdt-dialout-collector service user + tmpfiles.d config; preremove stops/disables the service; postremove cleans up only on purge), build helpers (install_deps.sh / build_collector.sh / make_packages.sh), and a proper man page (pkg/man/mdt_dialout_collector.1) covering synopsis, options, configuration, signals (SIGTERM/SIGINT/SIGUSR1), files, exit status, and examples.
  + Adding doc/INSTALL.md (recommended install flow per distro, post-install steps, where to find the man page and CONFIG-KEYS reference) and doc/INSTALL-FROM-SOURCE.md (developer / unsupported-distro builds via apt/dnf + cmake or autotools, plus the e2e and unit-test entry points). README rewritten to point at the package install with from-source as the secondary path.
  ! Marking install.sh as deprecated: kept in the tree as a developer convenience but no longer the recommended install path. A banner in the script header points operators at doc/INSTALL.md. The script still pins gRPC v1.45.2 and the hand-curated distro-detection matrix that the new packaging path obsoletes. doc/integration-with-pmtelemetryd.md and doc/Dependencies updated to reflect the package-first model.
  ! Removing the cfg_wrapper class entirely — it existed only as an intermediate between the global *_cfg_parameters maps (filled by cfg_handler) and the bridge's Options struct (consumed by pmacct). Nothing outside the bridge used it; the bridge round-tripped every value through cfg_wrapper.set_X() / cfg_wrapper.get_X() for no semantic gain. InitOptions now reads main_cfg_parameters / logs_cfg_parameters / data_manipulation_cfg_parameters directly via a 2-line `dup` lambda. Deleted src/cfgWrapper/{cfg_wrapper.cc, cfg_wrapper.h, Makefile.am, Makefile.in}; dropped from CMakeLists.txt + src/Makefile.am SUBDIRS + configure.ac AC_CONFIG_FILES. Bridge.cc 415 → 334 lines (-81); cfg_wrapper deletion -239 lines; total -320 lines. ABI preserved (Options struct field names unchanged).
  ! Refactoring the four Srv::*FsmCtrl() bodies in mdt_dialout_core.cc — each was a ~70-line copy with ~50 lines of identical kafka/zmq plumbing. Lifted to a VendorPlumbing struct (data_manipulation, data_wrapper, kafka_delivery, zmq_pusher, optional<KafkaProducer>, optional<zmq::socket_t>, delivery enum, label_encode bool, writer_id; ctor reads main_cfg_parameters once and picks the active delivery side). The CQ event loop became a small RunFsm<Stream> template helper (Stream::Spawn + while(cq->Next) loop). Each FsmCtrl now reads as ~17 lines: log thread id, construct VendorPlumbing, build per-vendor Context, call RunFsm. mdt_dialout_core.cc 1013 → 872 lines (-141). Validated: 8/8 unit tests, standalone 20/20, --pmtelemetryd 76/80.
  + Adding IPv6 listening-socket support. Operators can now bind any vendor's gRPC port on a v4 address ("0.0.0.0:10007"), the IPv6 wildcard ("[::]:10007" — Linux dual-stack accepts v4-mapped clients too) or a specific IPv6 address ("[2001:db8::1]:10007"). gRPC handles the address family transparently; the only project change was the peer-string parser.
