  ! Folding the per-message MetaData + AppendLabelMap two-parse pipeline into a single Json::Value pass via DataManipulation::BuildEnvelope. Previously every kafka-bound message went through three full JSON parse/serialize round-trips (vendor-specific producer → MetaData parse-then-discard validation + envelope write → AppendLabelMap parse + label add + write). Now the vendor helper writes its body once, then BuildEnvelope assembles the envelope (writer_id, seq, timestamp, telemetry_node/port, telemetry_data, optional label) in a single Json::Value and serializes. Two of the three round-trips eliminated. The validation-only parse is dropped — the vendor helpers all use Json::writeString which produces well-formed JSON by construction. Validated: standalone 80/80, --pmtelemetryd 76/80.
